13/01/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- During its session Monday (12 January), the BiH Presidency approved a programme of activities in 2004 related to Euro-Atlantic integration.
It includes a series of measures to be implemented in line with recommendations of the European Commission.
The presidency also adopted a plan for activities in the defence sector related to admission to NATO's Partnership for Peace programme.
In other news Monday, Deputy High Representative Donald Hays presented the list of economic reforms due to be implemented in BiH this year.
Priorities include indirect taxation reform, creation of a single business registration system and acceleration of the privatisation process.
(OHR Sources, Nezavisne novine - 13/01/04;
SRNA, BBC - 12/01/04)
